03:33.546 --> 03:35.874
The costume I found...
it's Ricky Spanish!

03:35.999 --> 03:37.916
It's Ricky Spanish!

03:39.552 --> 03:42.047
Ugh, yes!

03:42.172 --> 03:43.531
Get Ricky Spanish!

03:43.656 --> 03:46.658
He's the only one
this angry mob should be after!

03:54.667 --> 03:56.077
This is wonderful!

03:56.202 --> 03:57.912
I am actually eating enough food

03:58.037 --> 03:59.648
to produce a poop!

03:59.773 --> 04:01.750
So... Tungee,

04:01.875 --> 04:04.352
what made you decide to come find us?

04:04.477 --> 04:05.996
Your letters.

04:06.162 --> 04:09.057
Dear Tungee,
we think about you every day.

04:09.182 --> 04:10.992
We wish we could give you
a roof over your head

04:11.117 --> 04:14.095
and t-shirts from the teams that
actually won the Super Bowl.

04:14.220 --> 04:16.731
Yours always,
Stan and Francine Smith.

04:16.856 --> 04:18.533
Why would you write that?

04:18.658 --> 04:20.402
I didn't think he'd live past ten.

04:20.527 --> 04:22.787
Oh, Tungee.

04:22.912 --> 04:24.990
We're glad you're here but...

04:25.115 --> 04:26.891
How long you plan on staying?

04:27.016 --> 04:28.493
You said a short time, right, Tunj?

04:28.768 --> 04:31.153
Yes, yes, I will stay forever!

04:32.956 --> 04:34.699
Is there any chance
you're gonna surprise us

04:34.824 --> 04:35.901
and be the prince of Zamunda?

04:36.067 --> 04:37.903
None!

04:41.530 --> 04:43.499
Show your face, Ricky Spanish!

04:45.718 --> 04:47.379
Okay, I'm at the alley whe

04:47.504 --> 04:49.597
we rolled dice on
Paula Abdul's dead body.

04:49.722 --> 04:51.816
Gimme the clothes, gimme!

04:51.941 --> 04:52.851
We gotta get out of here!

04:53.125 --> 04:54.285
What's going on, Roger?

04:54.410 --> 04:55.879
Who is Ricky Spanish?

04:56.045 --> 04:58.223
The worst persona I've ever done.

04:58.348 --> 04:59.257
Oh, come on.

04:59.423 --> 05:00.492
It's true.

05:00.617 --> 05:02.694
He's a lying, thieving sociopath.

05:02.819 --> 05:04.329
There's hardly a person in this town

05:04.454 --> 05:06.197
who he hasn't stolen from, cheated...

05:06.322 --> 05:07.532
or worse...

05:07.657 --> 05:09.226
Everyone hates Ricky Spanish.

05:09.392 --> 05:11.519
Ricky Spanish...

05:13.429 --> 05:15.315
Come on!

05:15.481 --> 05:18.109
Wow. Sounds like Ricky Spanish...

05:18.275 --> 05:20.612
<i>Ricky Spanish...</i>

05:20.778 --> 05:22.480
... really is your
worst persona ever.

05:22.605 --> 05:23.932
Keep your voice down!

05:24.057 --> 05:25.659
These people will kill me
if they find out I'm...

05:25.825 --> 05:28.160
<i>Ricky Spanish...</i>

05:32.215 --> 05:33.658
Eh!

05:33.783 --> 05:35.794
Wait, you're burning up
Ricky Spanish?

05:35.960 --> 05:37.946
<i>Ricky Spanish...</i>

05:38.212 --> 05:39.297
I have no choice.

05:39.463 --> 05:40.715
I love being Ricky.

05:40.840 --> 05:42.167
I mean, the outfit alone...

05:42.292 --> 05:43.985
But everyone around here hates him.

05:44.110 --> 05:46.304
That's the downside
of living in a smallown.

05:46.429 --> 05:48.123
Everyone is in everybody's business.

05:48.248 --> 05:50.024
God, I want to move to New York.

05:50.149 --> 05:51.526
But I'm scared, ya know?

05:51.651 --> 05:53.495
It seems like something you do
if you have no money

05:53.620 --> 05:56.106
or a lot of money and
I'm sort of in between.

05:56.272 --> 05:57.632
You can still be Ricky.

05:57.757 --> 06:00.527
Just make him a better person,
then people will like him.

06:00.693 --> 06:02.779
Ricky can't be redeemed, Steve.

06:02.945 --> 06:04.355
I don't believe that.

06:04.480 --> 06:06.374
Everyone can change for the better.

06:06.499 --> 06:09.494
This guy's going to do it
and so can Ricky.

06:09.660 --> 06:11.653
<i>Ricky Spanish...</i>

06:13.890 --> 06:16.334
You... you really think I can change?

06:16.625 --> 06:18.636
Bitch, what did I just say?

06:18.761 --> 06:20.738
Come on, I'll help you make amends

06:20.863 --> 06:22.364
with every person you've wronged.

06:23.666 --> 06:24.642
Okay.

06:24.767 --> 06:25.710
Let's do it!

06:25.835 --> 06:28.012
Awesome!
This is gonna be great!

06:28.137 --> 06:32.142
And I guarantee you, everyone
you wronged will forgive you.

06:32.308 --> 06:33.067
Kill.

06:33.192 --> 06:34.018
You.

06:34.143 --> 06:35.069
Ricky.

06:35.194 --> 06:36.070
Spanish.

06:36.195 --> 06:37.071
Kill.

06:37.196 --> 06:38.056
You.

06:38.181 --> 06:40.308
Ricky... Spanish.

06:40.433 --> 06:43.445
This exercising to things
you hate is really working!

06:44.771 --> 06:45.864
Jean.

06:45.989 --> 06:46.898
Jackets.

06:47.023 --> 06:47.899
Timothy's.

06:48.024 --> 06:48.900
Bangs.

06:49.025 --> 06:49.901
Jean.

06:50.026 --> 06:50.902
Jackets.

06:51.027 --> 06:52.829
Timothy's bangs.

06:57.500 --> 06:58.826
Carol, I robbed.

06:58.951 --> 07:00.278
Eduardo, I stabbed.

07:00.403 --> 07:02.030
Tina, I taught how to kiss.

07:02.155 --> 07:04.449
Gave her some bad information,
never corrected it.

07:04.574 --> 07:06.274
She's out there darting
her tongue like this.

07:08.244 --> 07:10.338
Well, get ready, 'cause
we're gonna make amends

07:10.463 --> 07:11.673
with everyone on that list

07:11.798 --> 07:13.741
until Ricky Spanish is redeemed.

07:13.866 --> 07:16.102
Okay, who's first?

07:20.640 --> 07:21.524
Brian?

07:21.690 --> 07:22.525
It's me, Ri...

07:22.733 --> 07:24.903
Damn you, Ricky Spanish!

07:25.069 --> 07:27.288
He's here to apologize! Geez!

07:27.413 --> 07:29.140
What did Ricky do to you, anyway?

07:29.265 --> 07:31.451
Tijuana!
He did Tijuana to me!

07:31.768 --> 07:34.612
<i>Oh, we were having
ourselves a fine old time,</i>

07:34.737 --> 07:37.615
<i>down Mexico way.</i>

07:37.740 --> 07:39.384
Oh, I can take care of you.

07:39.509 --> 07:40.818
<i>Then, out of the blue,</i>

07:40.943 --> 07:42.244
<i>Ricky jumped me and left me stranded!</i>

07:47.617 --> 07:50.828
With no I.D., I was stuck
in TJ for six months!

07:50.953 --> 07:53.598
I had to work as the squeegee
boy at a donkey show.

07:53.823 --> 07:55.867
Every night,
watching a different girl

07:55.992 --> 07:58.937
sleep with the donkey I loved.

07:59.103 --> 08:01.506
Brian, I'm so sorry.

08:01.631 --> 08:04.575
I was a bad guy,
but I'm trying to change!

08:04.700 --> 08:05.910
Aw, hell, Ricky.

08:06.035 --> 08:07.645
I can't stay mad at you!

08:07.770 --> 08:11.449
I'm on way too many anti-psychotics!

08:13.033 --> 08:14.327
Yeah!

08:21.767 --> 08:23.111
Steve Smith!

08:23.236 --> 08:24.962
Ricky Spanish!

08:25.087 --> 08:27.265
We're doing cocaine
and shooting guns!

08:27.390 --> 08:28.508
Join us!

08:31.244 --> 08:35.472
I just met this woman, but I'm
already really into it!

08:39.268 --> 08:42.169
Avery, I'm here to apologize for...

08:44.407 --> 08:45.650
... for killing your wife.

08:45.775 --> 08:46.884
Killing my wife?!

08:47.009 --> 08:48.086
When?

08:48.211 --> 08:49.053
You seriously don't remember?

08:49.178 --> 08:50.555
Hey, man...

08:50.680 --> 08:52.115
It was her birthday...

08:52.381 --> 08:55.109
<i>and you know how I am
when I drink champagne...</i>

08:56.953 --> 09:01.232
Oh, yes, I seem to recall
something like that.

09:01.357 --> 09:03.101
So...
you're not mad at me?

09:03.226 --> 09:04.736
Why should I be?

09:04.861 --> 09:08.856
As you can see, everything in
my life is going perfectly.

09:16.513 --> 09:18.316
This is really working, Steve!

09:18.441 --> 09:20.051
They forgave me, and I feel great!

09:20.176 --> 09:21.419
See?

09:21.544 --> 09:23.321
I told you anyone can
change for the better.

09:23.446 --> 09:25.398
Okay, next up is Daniel.

09:25.564 --> 09:26.557
Daniel?!

09:26.682 --> 09:28.192
I can't face Daniel!

09:28.317 --> 09:29.994
What I did to him was too horrible!

09:30.119 --> 09:31.446
Skip down!
Skip down to someone else!

09:31.571 --> 09:32.480
No, forget it.

09:32.605 --> 09:33.648
Let's start a business.

09:33.773 --> 09:35.650
We'll buy a truck
and do pedicures in it.

09:35.775 --> 09:38.035
We'll call it "Nail Salon
Wheels Truck," I don't know!

09:38.160 --> 09:39.361
Wait, who's Daniel?

09:41.230 --> 09:43.775
We worked together
at Plantain Republic.

09:43.900 --> 09:46.761
He told me about a huge sweater
shipment and we stole it.

09:46.886 --> 09:49.330
But the heist went bad and I
pinned the whole thing on him.

09:49.455 --> 09:51.783
He's been in jail ever since.

09:51.908 --> 09:53.593
I can't do this anymore!

09:53.759 --> 09:55.136
I feel constricted!

09:55.261 --> 09:57.121
I can't breathe!

10:00.750 --> 10:03.528
That's just the cocoon you
feel around you, Roger.

10:03.653 --> 10:06.764
You're changing into something
better, like this little guy.

10:08.090 --> 10:08.942
You think?

10:09.108 --> 10:10.501
Yes!

10:10.626 --> 10:12.695
I know it's not easy, but you
have to stick it out.

10:12.995 --> 10:14.605
It's like <i>Saturday Night Live.</i>

10:14.730 --> 10:17.942
The opening sketch stinks,
the monologue is awful,

10:18.067 --> 10:19.544
but then Keenan does
"What up with that?"

10:19.669 --> 10:21.112
and it's all worth it.

10:21.237 --> 10:24.015
Okay... Okay...
I'll face Daniel...

10:24.140 --> 10:26.741
right after I finish huffing
whatever's in this bag.

10:37.010 --> 10:39.263
This water is wonderful!

10:39.388 --> 10:41.916
And there is not one parasite
swimming up my urethra!

10:42.041 --> 10:44.335
I love this place!

10:44.460 --> 10:48.456
Ugh! He's so positive and
grateful about everything.

10:48.581 --> 10:50.474
Yeah, I'm having a hard time
taking things for granted

10:50.599 --> 10:51.742
with this kid in the house.

10:51.867 --> 10:53.744
We gotta ditch him.

10:53.869 --> 10:55.062
Hey, Tungee!

10:55.187 --> 10:57.215
Want to run an errand
with Mama and Papa?

10:57.340 --> 10:58.683
An errand?
An errand?

10:58.808 --> 11:00.618
Yes! Yes!
Yes! Yes!

11:00.743 --> 11:01.986
What is this errand?!
Yes!

11:08.917 --> 11:10.561
Are you sure we can
just leave him here?

11:10.686 --> 11:11.996
He'll be fine.

11:12.121 --> 11:14.582
He can live off free food
samples, watch HD television...

11:14.707 --> 11:15.900
and look at the high ceiling...

11:16.025 --> 11:17.985
he can grow as tall
as he wants in here.

11:18.110 --> 11:20.513
Okay, let's just get this over with.

11:20.679 --> 11:23.190
Tungee, go get us a pair
of really rough dungarees

11:23.315 --> 11:24.892
and a ten-pack of snow tires.

11:25.017 --> 11:27.485
I will do it, Mr. and Lady Smith.

11:34.977 --> 11:37.572
Hey, how did you get
Daniel out so fast anyway?

11:37.697 --> 11:40.491
Let's just say I have
an in with the judge.

11:41.492 --> 11:43.644
I sentence you to life in prison.

11:50.242 --> 11:53.821
Oh, Edith, you are
the only thing in this world

11:53.946 --> 11:55.798
that makes sense to me.

11:55.964 --> 11:57.808
Welcome home, dear.

11:57.933 --> 11:59.802
Can I talk to you about something?

11:59.969 --> 12:02.747
You, y-you've been
married for 35 years?

12:02.872 --> 12:04.649
How do you even have the time?

12:04.774 --> 12:07.018
If it's important you find the time.

12:07.143 --> 12:08.144
Ricky!

12:08.310 --> 12:10.313
I should kill you right here.

12:11.731 --> 12:13.858
Please, Daniel, I got
you out of prison.

12:14.024 --> 12:16.319
You got me sent there
in the first place!

12:16.485 --> 12:18.145
I'll make it up to you, I swear.

12:18.270 --> 12:21.799
Give him a chance, sir,
he's a changed man.

12:21.924 --> 12:25.086
All right, I'll give you
a week to make it up to me,

12:25.211 --> 12:27.979
and if you don't, you die.

12:30.207 --> 12:33.678
Have you been in there
this whole time?

12:33.803 --> 12:35.004
Huh.

12:35.170 --> 12:37.081
Wait, so where did we park?

12:37.206 --> 12:38.866
Oh, that's right, we skipped here.

12:38.991 --> 12:42.428
♪ ♪

12:50.636 --> 12:52.513
Ma'am, you left your purse.

12:52.638 --> 12:53.664
Oh, thank you.

12:53.789 --> 12:55.466
I am such a ditz.

12:55.591 --> 12:57.694
I'd forget my own butt
if it wasn't so big.

13:00.062 --> 13:01.672
Ha-ha, made you look.

13:01.797 --> 13:03.032
It's normal.

13:03.198 --> 13:05.868
I'm Jenny.

13:10.139 --> 13:12.249
Jenny!

13:12.416 --> 13:13.884
I'm so proud of you.

13:14.009 --> 13:15.720
You've become a good person, Ricky.

13:15.845 --> 13:18.055
You've turned into a butterfly.

13:18.180 --> 13:20.091
Thanks for believing in me, Steve.

13:20.216 --> 13:21.359
Sure thing, bud.

13:21.484 --> 13:22.643
I'm gonna hit the jukebo

13:22.768 --> 13:24.845
see if they got any
Keith Sweat up in this piece.

13:24.970 --> 13:26.230
Nice kid.

13:26.355 --> 13:27.965
Yeah, yeah, listen, you
still have connections

13:28.090 --> 13:29.600
in shipping at Plantain Republic?

13:29.725 --> 13:31.335
Sure, why?

13:31.460 --> 13:32.520
'Cause I hear there's three tons

13:32.645 --> 13:34.422
of cashmere sweaters coming in.

13:34.547 --> 13:35.556
You find out where and when,

13:35.681 --> 13:37.150
we can take down the whole shipment.

13:37.316 --> 13:38.592
Are you crazy?

13:38.717 --> 13:40.628
Look, even if I was interested,

13:40.753 --> 13:44.532
no load of caj gets boosted
without someone going down.

13:44.657 --> 13:47.018
I'm not taking the fall
for you again, Ricky.

13:47.143 --> 13:48.386
You won't take the fall.

13:48.511 --> 13:50.371
That stupid kid will.

13:50.679 --> 13:54.125
♪ My body all
over your body, babe ♪

13:54.250 --> 13:57.194
♪ Your body all over
my body, babe. ♪

13:59.838 --> 14:02.500
What I did to you, we're
going to do to him.

14:02.625 --> 14:05.803
You are one cold son of a bitch.

14:05.928 --> 14:08.097
I'm Ricky Spanish.

14:08.330 --> 14:10.248
<i>Ricky Spanish.</i>

14:16.460 --> 14:17.857
This is awesome!

14:18.023 --> 14:20.227
I've never been night fishing before!

14:20.352 --> 14:21.819
You're going to love it, champ.

14:21.985 --> 14:23.197
Sweet kid.

14:23.322 --> 14:25.415
Too bad he's going to spend
the rest of his life in jail.

14:34.800 --> 14:36.743
Whoa, I'm sorry.

14:36.868 --> 14:37.711
Not our fault.

14:37.836 --> 14:38.812
We're both tired.

14:38.937 --> 14:41.181
Could happen to anybody.

14:41.306 --> 14:42.916
Yeah, I'm not going
to beat myself up,

14:43.041 --> 14:45.119
and if it happens again later,
it happens again later.

14:45.244 --> 14:47.387
Right.

14:47.512 --> 14:49.247
I hope it happens again.

14:56.355 --> 14:57.598
What's wrong?

14:57.723 --> 15:00.601
I don't know, it's just,
if Tungee were here,

15:00.726 --> 15:03.170
he would have made a
big fuss about dinner.

15:03.295 --> 15:06.006
All that smiling and positivity.

15:06.131 --> 15:08.675
I thought he was annoying,
but now I miss him.

15:08.800 --> 15:10.544
I miss him, too.

15:10.669 --> 15:12.212
Tungee was amazing.

15:12.337 --> 15:15.883
He was the only good thing
that ever happened to me.

15:16.008 --> 15:17.317
We have to get him back, Stan.

15:17.442 --> 15:20.454
Yes, yes, we're going to Costgo.

15:20.579 --> 15:23.090
Oh, Stan.

15:23.215 --> 15:25.959
Ha-ha-ha, I made it into the episode.

15:26.084 --> 15:27.361
Pay me, bitches.

15:27.486 --> 15:29.387
Ha-ha! Me, too.

15:32.357 --> 15:34.468
Hey, why, why are we at the docks?

15:34.593 --> 15:36.236
What's going on?

15:36.361 --> 15:40.189
What's going on is, we're
stealing cashmere sweaters.

15:40.355 --> 15:42.092
But, Ricky,
you've made so much progress.

15:42.217 --> 15:43.401
You've changed.

15:43.567 --> 15:44.895
People don't change, Steve.

15:45.020 --> 15:46.571
You're thinking of Changelings.

15:46.737 --> 15:51.200
No, no, no, no, you apologized
to people, you made amends.

15:51.366 --> 15:53.103
All part of the plan, you dope.

15:53.228 --> 15:55.556
I made up with Lewis
so he'd lend me his houseboat,

15:55.681 --> 15:57.157
Bullock so he'd give me these guns,

15:57.282 --> 15:59.276
and Daniel so he'd lead me
to this shipnt.

15:59.401 --> 16:00.811
You used me.

16:00.936 --> 16:02.646
Sorry, pal, but the whole time

16:02.771 --> 16:04.181
you thought you were redeeming me,

16:04.306 --> 16:06.850
you were helping me
put this together.

16:06.975 --> 16:10.454
Now it's time to say
good night, Steve.

16:10.579 --> 16:12.446
Daniel.

16:15.317 --> 16:17.094
Oh!
Good night, Steve.

16:17.219 --> 16:20.631
Daniel, no.

16:20.756 --> 16:21.915
I'm sorry, where are my manners?

16:22.040 --> 16:24.167
Good night, puddin'.

16:24.292 --> 16:26.169
For the love of... hit him!

16:26.294 --> 16:28.071
Hit him in the head with the shotgun!

16:30.115 --> 16:32.059
Y-You, uh, you made that
an uncomfortable experience

16:32.184 --> 16:33.827
for me, Daniel.

16:33.952 --> 16:35.262
Didn't have to be.

16:35.387 --> 16:36.996
Should have been fun.

16:39.748 --> 16:41.168
Tungee!

16:41.293 --> 16:43.070
Uh, sorry, folks, we're closed.

16:43.195 --> 16:46.923
Damn it, man, we left a ray
of Nigerian sunshine in here!

16:47.089 --> 16:48.841
Tungee!

16:49.007 --> 16:50.067
Tungee!

16:52.344 --> 16:53.988
Tungee, baby!

16:56.191 --> 16:57.600
Mister and Lady!

16:57.766 --> 16:58.819
Tungee!

16:58.944 --> 17:00.853
Mister and Lady!

17:01.019 --> 17:02.104
Tungee!

17:02.270 --> 17:03.940
Mister and Lady!

17:04.106 --> 17:05.816
Tungee!
Tungee!

17:05.982 --> 17:08.944
Mister...

17:09.109 --> 17:09.694
Tungee.

17:09.861 --> 17:14.032
... and Lady...

17:14.324 --> 17:15.076
Tungee!

17:15.282 --> 17:16.285
Mister and Lady.

17:16.451 --> 17:18.913
Tungee!

17:19.079 --> 17:21.290
♪ Mister and Lady. ♪

17:21.455 --> 17:22.342
Tungee!

17:22.467 --> 17:23.541
Tungee!

17:23.708 --> 17:25.920
Mister and Lady in robot voice.

17:26.086 --> 17:27.405
Tungee!

17:28.590 --> 17:29.924
Tun-jay!

17:30.090 --> 17:32.426
Aah, Mister and Lady!

17:34.177 --> 17:35.305
Oh, Tungee!
Tungee!

17:35.430 --> 17:37.556
Oh, Mister and Lady.

17:37.722 --> 17:40.360
Oh, Tungee, we missed you so much!

17:40.485 --> 17:43.521
Let's go home.

17:47.065 --> 17:48.618
Tungee, we're so sorry.

17:48.743 --> 17:50.270
You must have been so scared.

17:50.395 --> 17:53.606
Yeah, we're never going
to leave you again, ever.

17:53.731 --> 17:56.209
And I never want to leave you,

17:56.334 --> 18:00.380
the most generous,
wonderful people I have ever...

18:00.505 --> 18:01.781
Ugh, this guy.

18:01.906 --> 18:05.118
I forgot how much he sucked.

18:05.243 --> 18:06.136
Should we?

18:06.261 --> 18:07.838
I don't think we have a choice.

18:07.963 --> 18:10.923
One, two. three.

18:16.761 --> 18:18.415
I miss him.

18:18.540 --> 18:19.773
Me, too.

18:27.898 --> 18:31.610
Come on, little guy, we have to
stop Ricky before it's too late.

18:31.776 --> 18:34.498
Okay, finish up while I go
plant some sweaters on Steve.

18:34.623 --> 18:35.614
Why would you do that?

18:35.857 --> 18:37.667
So when the guards find
Steve on the boat,

18:37.792 --> 18:39.869
they'll think he's the one
who stole the shipment.

18:40.035 --> 18:41.371
Why did I waste my time

18:41.496 --> 18:43.073
reading you all those Nancy Drews?

18:43.198 --> 18:44.257
Ricky!

18:44.382 --> 18:45.492
What the Dickens?

18:45.617 --> 18:46.959
I thought you knocked
him out, Daniel.

18:47.125 --> 18:48.127
What the Dickens?!

18:48.293 --> 18:49.563
Ricky, don't do this.

18:49.688 --> 18:51.380
You can still be good, I know it.

18:51.546 --> 18:52.799
Sorry, Steve,

18:52.924 --> 18:54.967
some people are just bad
and they always will be.

18:55.133 --> 18:56.827
Grab him, Daniel.
Come here.

19:02.891 --> 19:04.101
Shh, keep it down.

19:04.267 --> 19:05.269
Hey!

19:05.435 --> 19:07.238
Run for it!

19:09.397 --> 19:10.691
They're gaining on us.

19:23.411 --> 19:24.580
Ricky, help!

19:24.746 --> 19:26.750
I believe in you.

19:26.875 --> 19:29.293
You are a butterfly!

19:31.503 --> 19:32.880
Oh, God!

19:34.382 --> 19:36.526
You came back for me.

19:36.651 --> 19:37.944
I knew you changed.

19:38.069 --> 19:40.137
I knew you... aah...!

19:48.478 --> 19:50.857
Ow, ow, ow!

19:52.065 --> 19:52.859
No!

20:18.059 --> 20:21.421
Kill. You.
Ricky. Spanish.

20:21.546 --> 20:23.490
<i>Two beautiful creatures</i>

20:23.615 --> 20:26.259
<i>trapped in a prison
of another's design</i>

20:26.384 --> 20:29.395
<i>like a madman lost in a supermarket.</i>

20:29.654 --> 20:34.284
<i>One is freed while the other
dies alone in a glass tomb,</i>

20:34.409 --> 20:36.953
<i>which used to contain farts.</i>

20:37.078 --> 20:39.156
<i>Perhaps it is fitting,</i>

20:39.281 --> 20:42.626
<i>for what was the butterfly
other than a symbol</i>

20:42.751 --> 20:47.380
<i>of the boy's innocence
that perished days before,</i>

20:47.505 --> 20:51.918
<i>killed by the very soul
he tried to save?</i>

20:52.043 --> 20:55.838
<i>Ricky Spanish.</i>

